args: All the stalls are ready, Yaten!
Nice. Then go help Natalie prep the floats.
Yaten, I've thought of some new dishes for\nthe festival. Would you care to try them?
Sure thing. I'll be along in a while.
Yaten! The florist's new work is finished!
Well, the festival is almost upon us.
Anticipation for it seems to have\nmade the town much livelier.
Maybe that's why more and more people\nhave been volunteering to help lately.
Yep. This is gonna be one for the books,\nso look forward to—
I saw them from the lookout tower!
They're still a ways away, but it's only\na matter of time before they arrive!
Just when life was getting back to normal!
We only survived by the skin of our teeth\nlast time—now they'll finish the job!
I can't believe it's come to this...
Can you help everyone evacuate into\nthe castle, {player_name}?
Of course. But what are YOU going to do?
I got my own job here in town.
I promised the folks here they'd have\nthe best festival around.
I can't let 'em down after getting\ntheir hopes up like that.
Staying alive is more important\nthan some festival, you fool!
Which is why you should get out of here.\nIf I wanna be a fool, that's my business.
But if I can protect the town while\nprotecting the festival, all the better.
Wait... You really just want to protect\nthe town, don't you?!
Get 'em out of here already,\n{player_name}! Move it!
I'm looking forward to the festival,\nand I'm gonna fight to save it!
You have my steel as well!
This is my home—I can't turn tail and run\nwhile an outsider risks his life for us.
I agree—we can't just throw away all\nthe progress we've made up to now.
I won't let our home be destroyed again!
You've made me realize this town\nmeant more to me than I thought.
My food stall is here, as well as\ndecades worth of family recipes.
We can't let those damn fiends take\nanything else from us!
Right then. All of you stay here and\nkeep the fiends from entering town\nand wrecking our festival stalls.
Me and Natalie'll go meet the enemy\noutside the gates.
At least this way the town should\navoid being caught in the crossfire.
Don't need to tell me twice!
That's my ma—Wait, what the hell are\nYOU doing here, {player_name}?!
The townsfolk asked me to help you.
They seem to have their defenses\nwell in hand, so I agreed.
I thought all them town types were a\nbuncha cowards, but they came through!
Nah, it wasn't me. All I did was remind\neverybody what the town means to 'em.
I put together a festival to fill 'em\nwith hope for their town's future...
And we won't let some fiend mess it up!
Then let's keep the town safe!
Ha ha! There's nothing like a good fight\nto get a festival started!
